column80: I  think shampoos for women are primarily intended for slightly longer and varied hair types and may cost a bit more than men's. While men and women are equal they are not the same. I don't think stereotyping has much to do with it. Many women may enjoy an ornate shampoo container and this may be a predominantly  feminine nature.
